    Data external to the XML instance document.
    Feature
    A region on a (potentially) two-dimensional map of MS1 scans, defined by the retention time, mass over charge and optionally a mass trace.
    FeatureList
    All the features identified on a single raw file or raw file group.
    FileFormat
    The format of the ExternalData file, for example "tiff" for image files.
    GlobalQuantLayer
    A QuantLayer in which different data types are allowed in each column.

    IdentificationFile
    A single identification file associated with this analysis.
    IdentificationFiles
    All identification files associated with this quantitation analysis to be referenced elsewhere.
    IdentificationRef
    A reference to an external identification file defined in the document, plus a unique identifier for the object in that file, such as an ID of a SpectrumIdentificationItem, ProteinDetectionHypothesis or ProteinAmbiguityGroup in mzIdentML.
    IdOnly
    Other classes in the model can be specified as sub-classes, inheriting from IdOnly.
    InputFiles
    All the raw files, identification files and databases used in the quantitation.
    Label
    A specification of labels or tags used to define the assay within the raw file, such as heavy labelling or iTRAQ tag mass.
    MethodFile
    A single methods file associated with this analysis e.g.
    MethodFiles
    All methods files associated with this quantitation analysis to be referenced elsewhere, for example used to describe TraML files used in SRM analysis.
    Modification
    A molecule modification specification.
    ModParam
    The modification searched for or used to define the label or tag for quantification.
    MzQuantML
    Root element of the instance document.
    ObjectFactory
    This object contains factory methods for each Java content interface and Java element interface generated in the uk.ac.liv.jmzqml.model.mzqml package.
    Organization
    Organizations are entities like companies, universities, government agencies.

    Helper type to allow either a cvParam or a userParam to be provided for an element.
    ParamList
    Helper type to allow multiple cvParams or userParams to be given for an element.
    ParentOrganization
    The containing organization (the university or business which a lab belongs to, etc.)
    PeptideConsensus
    An element representing a peptide in different assays that may or may not have been identified.
    PeptideConsensusList
    The list of all peptides for which quantitation values are reported.

    A person's name and contact details.
    ProcessingMethod
    Description of one step within the data processing pipeline.

    A grouping of quantified proteins based on ambiguous assignment of peptide evidence to protein identification.
    ProteinGroupList
    The list of all groups of proteins with conflicting evidence for which quantitation values are being reported along with quantitative values about those protein groups.

    SmallMolecule
